text.tspan: Level k: There are ? Nodes, if this level is full
If we have a height of L in our tree and fill up all the levels, then
we have 1 + 2 + 4 + ... + 2^L nodes, which is 2^{L+1} - 1 nodes
Def. Balanced Tree: A tree with all but the lowest level completely filled
Lemma: A balanced tree with N nodes has height h that is O(log(N))
